review_blob: This is, hands down, my favorite milk stout. Perfect sweetness from the milk sugars, well balanced and rich. Poured with a head, it's almost too pretty to drink.
This is a pretty solid big IPA. Hoppy aroma, piney, slightly floral middle. Pleasantly bitter finish.
One of my absolute favorites. Great combo of happiness and rich malty flavor. Roasty, a bit nutty in the middle.
A very good roasty, malty Porter. Smooth rich finish. Sierra Nevada knows their stuff!
It is rare to find a wheat beer this good. The aroma is the only really sweet part of this beer. The blueberry flavor is present, but not overpowering of fruity. It's so well balanced. Nice job!
Much more complex than your average wheat beer, which is to be expected of Ommegang. A somewhat sweet, citrus wheat beer with unfiltered character.
Aside from it's lovely color and a bit of floral taste in the middle, there isn't much to it other than a whole lot of hoppy bitterness. The finish is particularly bitter.
Absolutely one of my top two favorite Belgians, and an all-time favorite beer. It hits heavy, but the complex, sweet middle will keep you going through til the last drop.

Bottle. This is a great beer to get your skeptical dad to try something other than bud light. It's a light, easy drinking beer with citrus notes that make it much more interesting than most light American lagers. Good for a hot day.
One of my absolute favorite porters, and I love my porters. Very smooth, malty, and rich. The finish stays with you (and I'm glad it does).
Starts malty. The middle is typical bitter hoppy IPA but with other flavors in the finish I can't quite pinpoint that make it more interesting than the average IPA.
Very accessible, easy to drink IPA. Hoppy without too much bite in the finish. A bit fruity and sweet in the middle.
Typical ale aroma with a sweet, caramel malty flavor. Hints of banana. Great example of an English ale that's been done right.
My favorite beer out of Newburgh Brewery. It's got a coffee aroma. The taste is very malty, dark chocolate, and roasty. Surprisingly sweet finish. It's very drinkable for an imperial stout.
